6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Crello and Framer share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Brand Kit, Collaboration. Where Crello pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Stock Assets, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Framer uniquely offers Ai Generation and Responsive and Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Crello holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Framer scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Crello and Framer offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Crello's free tier and Framer's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
